functions.name: ImGui_InputTextFlags_CallbackCompletion
functions.description: Callback on pressing TAB (for completion handling).

functions.name: ImGui_InputTextFlags_CallbackEdit
functions.description: Callback on any edit. Note that InputText already returns true on edit +you can always use IsItemEdited. The callback is useful to manipulate theunderlying buffer while focus is active.

functions.name: ImGui_InputTextFlags_CallbackHistory
functions.description: Callback on pressing Up/Down arrows (for history handling).

functions.name: ImGui_InputTextFlags_CharsHexadecimal
functions.description: Allow 0123456789ABCDEFabcdef.

functions.name: ImGui_InputTextFlags_CharsNoBlank
functions.description: Filter out spaces, tabs.

functions.name: ImGui_InputTextFlags_CharsScientific
functions.description: Allow 0123456789.+-*/eE (Scientific notation input).

functions.name: ImGui_InputTextFlags_CharsUppercase
functions.description: Turn a..z into A..Z.

functions.name: ImGui_InputTextFlags_CtrlEnterForNewLine
functions.description: In multi-line mode, unfocus with Enter, add new line with Ctrl+Enter(default is opposite: unfocus with Ctrl+Enter, add line with Enter).

functions.name: ImGui_InputTextFlags_DisplayEmptyRefVal
functions.description: InputDouble(), InputInt() etc. only: when value is zero, do not display it.Generally used with InputTextFlags_ParseEmptyRefVal.

functions.name: ImGui_InputTextFlags_ElideLeft
functions.description: When text doesn't fit, elide left side to ensure right side stays visible.Useful for path/filenames. Single-line only!

functions.name: ImGui_InputTextFlags_EnterReturnsTrue
functions.description: Return true when Enter is pressed (as opposed to every time the value wasmodified). Consider using IsItemDeactivatedAfterEdit instead!

functions.name: ImGui_InputTextFlags_EscapeClearsAll
functions.description: Escape key clears content if not empty, and deactivate otherwise(constrast to default behavior of Escape to revert).

functions.name: ImGui_InputTextFlags_NoHorizontalScroll
functions.description: Disable following the cursor horizontally.

functions.name: ImGui_InputTextFlags_NoUndoRedo
functions.description: Disable undo/redo. Note that input text owns the text data while active.

functions.name: ImGui_InputTextFlags_ParseEmptyRefVal
functions.description: InputDouble(), InputInt() etc. only: parse empty string as zero value.

functions.name: ImGui_InputTextFlags_Password
functions.description: Password mode, display all characters as '*'.

functions.name: ImGui_InputTextFlags_ReadOnly
functions.description: Read-only mode.

functions.name: ImGui_InvisibleButton
functions.description: Flexible button behavior without the visuals, frequently useful to buildcustom behaviors using the public api (along with IsItemActive, IsItemHovered, etc.).

functions.name: ImGui_IsAnyMouseDown
functions.description: Is any mouse button held?

functions.name: ImGui_IsItemActivated
functions.description: Was the last item just made active (item was previously inactive).

functions.name: ImGui_IsItemActive
functions.description: Is the last item active? (e.g. button being held, text field being edited.This will continuously return true while holding mouse button on an item.Items that don't interact will always return false.

functions.name: ImGui_IsItemClicked
functions.description: Is the last item clicked? (e.g. button/node just clicked on)== IsMouseClicked(mouse_button) && IsItemHovered().

functions.name: ImGui_IsItemDeactivated
functions.description: Was the last item just made inactive (item was previously active).Useful for Undo/Redo patterns with widgets that require continuous editing.

functions.name: ImGui_IsItemDeactivatedAfterEdit
functions.description: Was the last item just made inactive and made a value change when it wasactive? (e.g. Slider/Drag moved).

functions.description: Did the last item modify its underlying value this frame? or was pressed?This is generally the same as the "bool" return value of many widgets.

functions.name: ImGui_IsItemFocused

functions.name: ImGui_IsItemHovered
functions.description: Is the last item hovered? (and usable, aka not blocked by a popup, etc.).See HoveredFlags_* for more options.

functions.name: ImGui_IsItemToggledOpen
functions.description: Was the last item open state toggled? Set by TreeNode.

functions.description: Is the last item visible? (items may be out of sight because of clipping/scrolling)

functions.name: ImGui_IsKeyChordPressed

functions.name: ImGui_IsKeyDown
functions.description: Is key being held.

functions.description: Was key pressed (went from !Down to Down)?If repeat=true, uses ConfigVar_KeyRepeatDelay / ConfigVar_KeyRepeatRate.

functions.name: ImGui_IsKeyReleased
functions.description: Was key released (went from Down to !Down)?

functions.name: ImGui_IsMouseClicked
functions.description: Did mouse button clicked? (went from !Down to Down).Same as GetMouseClickedCount() == 1.

functions.name: ImGui_IsMouseDoubleClicked
functions.description: Did mouse button double-clicked? Same as GetMouseClickedCount() == 2.(Note that a double-click will also report IsMouseClicked() == true)

functions.name: ImGui_IsMouseDown
functions.description: Is mouse button held?

functions.name: ImGui_IsMouseDragging
functions.description: Is mouse dragging? (uses ConfigVar_MouseDragThreshold if lock_threshold < 0.0)

functions.name: ImGui_IsMouseHoveringRect
functions.description: Is mouse hovering given bounding rect (in screen space).Clipped by current clipping settings, but disregarding of other considerationof focus/window ordering/popup-block.

functions.name: ImGui_IsMouseReleased
functions.description: Did mouse button released? (went from Down to !Down)

functions.name: ImGui_IsMouseReleasedWithDelay
functions.description: Delayed mouse release (use sparingly!). Generally used with`delay >= ConfigVar_MouseDoubleClickTime` + combined with a`GetMouseClickedCount()==1` test. This is a very rarely used UI idiom,but some apps use this: e.g. MS Explorer single click on an icon to rename.

functions.name: ImGui_IsPopupOpen

functions.name: ImGui_IsRectVisible
functions.description: Test if rectangle (of given size, starting from cursor position) isvisible / not clipped.

functions.name: ImGui_IsRectVisibleEx
functions.description: Test if rectangle (in screen space) is visible / not clipped. to performcoarse clipping on user's side.

functions.name: ImGui_IsWindowAppearing

functions.name: ImGui_IsWindowDocked

functions.description: See also Mod_Shift

functions.description: - items_count: Use INT_MAX from NumericLimits_Int if you don't know how manyitems you have (in which case the cursor won't be advanced in the final step,and you can call SeekCursorForItem manually if you need)- items_height: Use -1.0 to be calculated automatically on first step.Otherwise pass in the distance between your items, typicallyGetTextLineHeightWithSpacing or GetFrameHeightWithSpacing.

functions.name: ImGui_ListClipper_IncludeItemsByIndex
functions.description: See ListClipper_IncludeItemByIndex.

functions.name: ImGui_ListClipper_SeekCursorForItem
functions.description: Seek cursor toward given item. This is automatically called while stepping.The only reason to call this is: you can use ListClipper_Begin(INT_MAX) if youdon't know item count ahead of time. In this case, after all steps are done,you'll want to call SeekCursorForItem(items_count).

functions.name: ImGui_ListClipper_Step
functions.description: Call until it returns false. The display_start/display_end fields fromListClipper_GetDisplayRange will be set and you can process/draw those items.

functions.name: ImGui_SetColorEditOptions
functions.description: Picker type, etc. User will be able to change many settings, unless you passthe _NoOptions flag to your calls.

functions.name: ImGui_SetCursorPos
functions.description: Cursor position in window

functions.name: ImGui_SetCursorPosX
functions.description: Cursor X position in window

functions.name: ImGui_SetCursorPosY
functions.description: Cursor Y position in window

functions.name: ImGui_SetCursorScreenPos
functions.description: Cursor position in absolute screen coordinates.

functions.name: ImGui_SetDragDropPayload
functions.description: The type is a user defined string of maximum 32 characters.Strings starting with '_' are reserved for dear imgui internal types.Data is copied and held by imgui.

functions.name: ImGui_SetItemDefaultFocus
functions.description: Make last item the default focused item of a newly appearing window.

functions.name: ImGui_SetItemTooltip
functions.description: Set a text-only tooltip if preceding item was hovered.Override any previous call to SetTooltip(). Shortcut for`if (IsItemHovered(HoveredFlags_ForTooltip)) { SetTooltip(...); }`.

functions.name: ImGui_SetKeyboardFocusHere
functions.description: Focus keyboard on the next widget. Use positive 'offset' to access subcomponents of a multiple component widget. Use -1 to access previous widget.

functions.name: ImGui_SetMouseCursor
functions.description: Set desired mouse cursor shape. See MouseCursor_* for possible values.

functions.name: ImGui_SetNavCursorVisible
functions.description: Alter visibility of keyboard/gamepad cursor. By default: shown when using anarrow key, hidden when clicking with the mouse.

functions.name: ImGui_SetNextFrameWantCaptureKeyboard
functions.description: Request capture of keyboard shortcuts in REAPER's global scope for the next frame.

functions.name: ImGui_SetNextItemAllowOverlap
functions.description: Allow next item to be overlapped by a subsequent item.Useful with invisible buttons, selectable, treenode covering an area wheresubsequent items may need to be added. Note that both Selectable() and TreeNode()have dedicated flags doing this.

functions.name: ImGui_SetNextItemOpen
functions.description: Set next TreeNode/CollapsingHeader open state.Can also be done with the TreeNodeFlags_DefaultOpen flag.

functions.name: ImGui_SetNextItemWidth
functions.description: Set width of the _next_ common large "item+label" widget.

functions.name: ImGui_SetNextWindowBgAlpha
functions.description: Set next window background color alpha. Helper to easily override the Alphacomponent of Col_WindowBg/Col_ChildBg/Col_PopupBg.You may also use WindowFlags_NoBackground for a fully transparent window.

functions.name: ImGui_SetNextWindowCollapsed
functions.description: Set next window collapsed state.

functions.name: ImGui_SetNextWindowContentSize
functions.description: Set next window content size (~ scrollable client area, which enforce therange of scrollbars). Not including window decorations (title bar, menu bar,etc.) nor StyleVar_WindowPadding. set an axis to 0.0 to leave it automatic.

functions.name: ImGui_SetNextWindowFocus
functions.description: Set next window to be focused / top-most.

functions.name: ImGui_SetNextWindowPos
functions.description: Set next window position. Use pivot=(0.5,0.5) to center on given point, etc.

functions.name: ImGui_SetNextWindowScroll
functions.description: Set next window scrolling value (use < 0.0 to not affect a given axis).

functions.name: ImGui_SetNextWindowSize
functions.description: Set next window size. set axis to 0.0 to force an auto-fit on this axis.

functions.name: ImGui_SetNextWindowSizeConstraints
functions.description: Set next window size limits. Use 0.0 or FLT_MAX (second return value ofNumericLimits_Float) if you don't want limits.

functions.name: ImGui_SetScrollFromPosX
functions.description: Adjust scrolling amount to make given position visible.Generally GetCursorStartPos() + offset to compute a valid position.

functions.name: ImGui_SetScrollFromPosY
functions.description: Adjust scrolling amount to make given position visible.Generally GetCursorStartPos() + offset to compute a valid position.

functions.name: ImGui_SetScrollHereX
functions.description: Adjust scrolling amount to make current cursor position visible.center_x_ratio=0.0: left, 0.5: center, 1.0: right.When using to make a "default/current item" visible,consider using SetItemDefaultFocus instead.

functions.name: ImGui_SetScrollHereY
functions.description: Adjust scrolling amount to make current cursor position visible.center_y_ratio=0.0: top, 0.5: center, 1.0: bottom.When using to make a "default/current item" visible,consider using SetItemDefaultFocus instead.

functions.name: ImGui_SetScrollX
functions.description: Set scrolling amount [0 .. GetScrollMaxX()]

functions.name: ImGui_SetScrollY
functions.description: Set scrolling amount [0 .. GetScrollMaxY()]

functions.name: ImGui_SetTabItemClosed
functions.description: Notify TabBar or Docking system of a closed tab/window ahead(useful to reduce visual flicker on reorderable tab bars).For tab-bar: call after BeginTabBar and before Tab submissions.Otherwise call with a window name.

functions.name: ImGui_SetTooltip
functions.description: Set a text-only tooltip. Often used after a IsItemHovered() check.Override any previous call to SetTooltip.

functions.name: ImGui_SetWindowCollapsed
functions.description: (Not recommended) Set current window collapsed state.Prefer using SetNextWindowCollapsed.

functions.name: ImGui_SetWindowCollapsedEx
functions.description: Set named window collapsed state.

functions.name: ImGui_SetWindowFocus
functions.description: (Not recommended) Set current window to be focused / top-most.Prefer using SetNextWindowFocus.

functions.name: ImGui_SetWindowFocusEx
functions.description: Set named window to be focused / top-most. Use an empty name to remove focus.

functions.name: ImGui_SetWindowPos
functions.description: (Not recommended) Set current window position - call within Begin/End.Prefer using SetNextWindowPos, as this may incur tearing and minor side-effects.

functions.name: ImGui_SetWindowPosEx
functions.description: Set named window position.

functions.name: ImGui_SetWindowSize
functions.description: (Not recommended) Set current window size - call within Begin/End.Set size_w and size_h to 0 to force an auto-fit.Prefer using SetNextWindowSize, as this may incur tearing and minor side-effects.

functions.name: ImGui_SetWindowSizeEx
functions.description: Set named window size. Set axis to 0.0 to force an auto-fit on this axis.

functions.name: ImGui_ShowAboutWindow
functions.description: Create About window.Display ReaImGui version, Dear ImGui version, credits and build/system information.

functions.name: ImGui_ShowDebugLogWindow
functions.description: Create Debug Log window. display a simplified log of important dear imgui events.

functions.name: ImGui_ShowIDStackToolWindow
functions.description: Create Stack Tool window. Hover items with mouse to query information aboutthe source of their unique ID.

functions.name: ImGui_ShowMetricsWindow
functions.description: Create Metrics/Debugger window.Display Dear ImGui internals: windows, draw commands, various internal state, etc.

functions.name: ImGui_SliderFlags_AlwaysClamp
functions.description: SliderFlags_ClampOnInput | SliderFlags_ClampZeroRange

functions.name: ImGui_SliderFlags_ClampOnInput
functions.description: Clamp value to min/max bounds when input manually with Ctrl+Click.By default Ctrl+Click allows going out of bounds.

functions.name: ImGui_SliderFlags_ClampZeroRange
functions.description: Clamp even if min==max==0. Otherwise due to legacy reason Drag* functionsdon't clamp with those values. When your clamping limits are dynamic youalmost always want to use it.

functions.name: ImGui_SliderFlags_Logarithmic
functions.description: Make the widget logarithmic (linear otherwise).Consider using SliderFlags_NoRoundToFormat with this if using a format-stringwith small amount of digits.

functions.name: ImGui_SliderFlags_NoInput
functions.description: Disable CTRL+Click or Enter key allowing to input text directly into the widget.

functions.name: ImGui_SliderFlags_NoRoundToFormat
functions.description: Disable rounding underlying value to match precision of the display formatstring (e.g. %.3f values are rounded to those 3 digits).

functions.name: ImGui_SliderFlags_NoSpeedTweaks
functions.description: Disable keyboard modifiers altering tweak speed.Useful if you want to alter tweak speed yourself based on your own logic.

functions.name: ImGui_SliderFlags_WrapAround
functions.description: Enable wrapping around from max to min and from min to max.Only supported by Drag* functions for now.

functions.name: ImGui_SmallButton
functions.description: Button with StyleVar_FramePadding.y == 0 to easily embed within text.

functions.name: ImGui_SortDirection_Ascending
functions.description: Ascending = 0->9, A->Z etc.

functions.name: ImGui_SortDirection_Descending
functions.description: Descending = 9->0, Z->A etc.

functions.name: ImGui_Spacing
functions.description: Add vertical spacing.

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_Alpha
functions.description: Global alpha applies to everything in Dear ImGui.

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_ButtonTextAlign
functions.description: Alignment of button text when button is larger than text.Defaults to (0.5, 0.5) (centered).

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_CellPadding
functions.description: Padding within a table cell.CellPadding.x is locked for entire table.CellPadding.y may be altered between different rows.

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_ChildBorderSize
functions.description: Thickness of border around child windows. Generally set to 0.0 or 1.0.(Other values are not well tested and more CPU/GPU costly).

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_ChildRounding
functions.description: Radius of child window corners rounding. Set to 0.0 to have rectangular windows.

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_DisabledAlpha
functions.description: Additional alpha multiplier applied by BeginDisabled.Multiply over current value of Alpha.

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_FrameBorderSize
functions.description: Thickness of border around frames. Generally set to 0.0 or 1.0.(Other values are not well tested and more CPU/GPU costly).

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_FramePadding
functions.description: Padding within a framed rectangle (used by most widgets).

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_FrameRounding
functions.description: Radius of frame corners rounding.Set to 0.0 to have rectangular frame (used by most widgets).

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_GrabMinSize
functions.description: Minimum width/height of a grab box for slider/scrollbar.

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_GrabRounding
functions.description: Radius of grabs corners rounding. Set to 0.0 to have rectangular slider grabs.

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_ImageBorderSize
functions.description: Thickness of border around Image calls.

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_IndentSpacing
functions.description: Horizontal indentation when e.g. entering a tree node.Generally == (GetFontSize + StyleVar_FramePadding.x*2).

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_ItemInnerSpacing
functions.description: Horizontal and vertical spacing between within elements of a composed widget(e.g. a slider and its label).

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_ItemSpacing
functions.description: Horizontal and vertical spacing between widgets/lines.

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_PopupBorderSize
functions.description: Thickness of border around popup/tooltip windows. Generally set to 0.0 or 1.0.(Other values are not well tested and more CPU/GPU costly).

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_PopupRounding
functions.description: Radius of popup window corners rounding.(Note that tooltip windows use StyleVar_WindowRounding.)

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_ScrollbarRounding
functions.description: Radius of grab corners for scrollbar.

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_ScrollbarSize
functions.description: Width of the vertical scrollbar, Height of the horizontal scrollbar.

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_SelectableTextAlign
functions.description: Alignment of selectable text. Defaults to (0.0, 0.0) (top-left aligned).It's generally important to keep this left-aligned if you want to laymultiple items on a same line.

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_SeparatorTextAlign
functions.description: Alignment of text within the separator.Defaults to (0.0, 0.5) (left aligned, center).

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_SeparatorTextBorderSize
functions.description: Thickness of border in SeparatorText()

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_SeparatorTextPadding
functions.description: Horizontal offset of text from each edge of the separator + spacing on otheraxis. Generally small values. .y is recommended to be == StyleVar_FramePadding.y.

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_TabBarBorderSize
functions.description: Thickness of tab-bar separator, which takes on the tab active color to denote focus.

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_TabBarOverlineSize
functions.description: Thickness of tab-bar overline, which highlights the selected tab-bar.

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_TabBorderSize
functions.description: Thickness of border around tabs.

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_TabRounding
functions.description: Radius of upper corners of a tab. Set to 0.0 to have rectangular tabs.

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_TableAngledHeadersAngle
functions.description: Angle of angled headers (supported values range from -50.0 degrees to +50.0 degrees).

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_TableAngledHeadersTextAlign
functions.description: Alignment of angled headers within the cell

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_TreeLinesRounding
functions.description: Radius of lines connecting child nodes to the vertical line.

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_TreeLinesSize
functions.description: Thickness of outlines when using TreeNodeFlags_DrawLines.

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_WindowBorderSize
functions.description: Thickness of border around windows. Generally set to 0.0 or 1.0.(Other values are not well tested and more CPU/GPU costly).

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_WindowMinSize
functions.description: Minimum window size. This is a global setting.If you want to constrain individual windows, use SetNextWindowSizeConstraints.

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_WindowPadding
functions.description: Padding within a window.

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_WindowRounding
functions.description: Radius of window corners rounding. Set to 0.0 to have rectangular windows.Large values tend to lead to variety of artifacts and are not recommended.

functions.name: ImGui_StyleVar_WindowTitleAlign
functions.description: Alignment for title bar text.Defaults to (0.0,0.5) for left-aligned,vertically centered.

functions.name: ImGui_TabBarFlags_AutoSelectNewTabs
functions.description: Automatically select new tabs when they appear.

functions.name: ImGui_TabBarFlags_DrawSelectedOverline
functions.description: Draw selected overline markers over selected tab

functions.name: ImGui_TabBarFlags_FittingPolicyResizeDown
functions.description: Resize tabs when they don't fit.

functions.name: ImGui_TabBarFlags_FittingPolicyScroll
functions.description: Add scroll buttons when tabs don't fit.

functions.name: ImGui_TabBarFlags_NoCloseWithMiddleMouseButton
functions.description: Disable behavior of closing tabs (that are submitted with p_open != nil)with middle mouse button. You may handle this behavior manually on user'sside with if(IsItemHovered() && IsMouseClicked(2)) p_open = false.

functions.name: ImGui_TabBarFlags_NoTabListScrollingButtons
functions.description: Disable scrolling buttons (apply when fitting policy isTabBarFlags_FittingPolicyScroll).

functions.name: ImGui_TabBarFlags_NoTooltip
functions.description: Disable tooltips when hovering a tab.

functions.name: ImGui_TabBarFlags_Reorderable
functions.description: Allow manually dragging tabs to re-order them + New tabs are appended atthe end of list.

functions.name: ImGui_TabBarFlags_TabListPopupButton
functions.description: Disable buttons to open the tab list popup.

functions.name: ImGui_TabItemButton
functions.description: Create a Tab behaving like a button. Return true when clicked.Cannot be selected in the tab bar.

functions.name: ImGui_TabItemFlags_Leading
functions.description: Enforce the tab position to the left of the tab bar (after the tab list popup button).

functions.name: ImGui_TabItemFlags_NoAssumedClosure
functions.description: Tab is selected when trying to close + closure is not immediately assumed(will wait for user to stop submitting the tab).Otherwise closure is assumed when pressing the X, so if you keep submittingthe tab may reappear at end of tab bar.

functions.name: ImGui_TabItemFlags_NoCloseWithMiddleMouseButton
functions.description: Disable behavior of closing tabs (that are submitted with p_open != nil) withmiddle mouse button. You can still repro this behavior on user's side withif(IsItemHovered() && IsMouseClicked(2)) p_open = false.

functions.name: ImGui_TabItemFlags_NoPushId
functions.description: Don't call PushID()/PopID() on BeginTabItem/EndTabItem.

functions.name: ImGui_TabItemFlags_NoReorder
functions.description: Disable reordering this tab or having another tab cross over this tab.

functions.name: ImGui_TabItemFlags_NoTooltip
functions.description: Disable tooltip for the given tab.

functions.name: ImGui_TabItemFlags_SetSelected
functions.description: Trigger flag to programmatically make the tab selected when calling BeginTabItem.

functions.name: ImGui_TabItemFlags_Trailing
functions.description: Enforce the tab position to the right of the tab bar (before the scrolling buttons).

functions.name: ImGui_TabItemFlags_UnsavedDocument
functions.description: Display a dot next to the title + set TabItemFlags_NoAssumedClosure.

functions.name: ImGui_TableAngledHeadersRow
functions.description: Submit a row with angled headers for every column with theTableColumnFlags_AngledHeader flag. Must be the first row.

functions.name: ImGui_TableBgTarget_CellBg
functions.description: Set cell background color (top-most color).

functions.name: ImGui_TableBgTarget_RowBg0
functions.description: Set row background color 0 (generally used for background,automatically set when TableFlags_RowBg is used).

functions.name: ImGui_TableBgTarget_RowBg1
functions.description: Set row background color 1 (generally used for selection marking).

functions.name: ImGui_TableColumnFlags_AngledHeader
functions.description: TableHeadersRow will submit an angled header row for this column.Note this will add an extra row.

functions.name: ImGui_TableColumnFlags_DefaultHide
functions.description: Default as a hidden/disabled column.

functions.name: ImGui_TableColumnFlags_DefaultSort
functions.description: Default as a sorting column.

functions.name: ImGui_TableColumnFlags_Disabled
functions.description: Overriding/master disable flag: hide column, won't show in context menu(unlike calling TableSetColumnEnabled which manipulates the user accessible state).

functions.name: ImGui_TableColumnFlags_IndentDisable
functions.description: Ignore current Indent value when entering cell (default for columns > 0).Indentation changes _within_ the cell will still be honored.

functions.name: ImGui_TableColumnFlags_IndentEnable
functions.description: Use current Indent value when entering cell (default for column 0).

functions.name: ImGui_TableColumnFlags_IsEnabled
functions.description: Status: is enabled == not hidden by user/api (referred to as "Hide" in_DefaultHide and _NoHide) flags.

functions.name: ImGui_TableColumnFlags_IsHovered
functions.description: Status: is hovered by mouse.

functions.name: ImGui_TableColumnFlags_IsSorted
functions.description: Status: is currently part of the sort specs.

functions.name: ImGui_TableColumnFlags_IsVisible
functions.description: Status: is visible == is enabled AND not clipped by scrolling.

functions.name: ImGui_TableColumnFlags_NoClip
functions.description: Disable clipping for this column(all NoClip columns will render in a same draw command).

functions.name: ImGui_TableColumnFlags_NoHeaderLabel
functions.description: TableHeadersRow will submit an empty label for this column.Convenient for some small columns.Name will still appear in context menu or in angled headers.You may append into this cell by calling TableSetColumnIndex right afterthe TableHeadersRow call.

functions.name: ImGui_TableColumnFlags_NoHeaderWidth
functions.description: Disable header text width contribution to automatic column width.

functions.name: ImGui_TableColumnFlags_NoHide
functions.description: Disable ability to hide/disable this column.

functions.name: ImGui_TableColumnFlags_NoReorder
functions.description: Disable manual reordering this column, this will also prevent other columnsfrom crossing over this column.

functions.name: ImGui_TableColumnFlags_NoResize
functions.description: Disable manual resizing.

functions.name: ImGui_TableColumnFlags_NoSort
functions.description: Disable ability to sort on this field(even if TableFlags_Sortable is set on the table).

functions.name: ImGui_TableColumnFlags_NoSortAscending
functions.description: Disable ability to sort in the ascending direction.

functions.name: ImGui_TableColumnFlags_NoSortDescending
functions.description: Disable ability to sort in the descending direction.

functions.name: ImGui_TableColumnFlags_PreferSortAscending
functions.description: Make the initial sort direction Ascending when first sorting on this column (default).

functions.name: ImGui_TableColumnFlags_PreferSortDescending
functions.description: Make the initial sort direction Descending when first sorting on this column.

functions.name: ImGui_TableColumnFlags_WidthFixed
functions.description: Column will not stretch. Preferable with horizontal scrolling enabled(default if table sizing policy is _SizingFixedFit and table is resizable).

functions.name: ImGui_TableColumnFlags_WidthStretch
functions.description: Column will stretch. Preferable with horizontal scrolling disabled(default if table sizing policy is _SizingStretchSame or _SizingStretchProp).

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_Borders
functions.description: Draw all borders.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_BordersH
functions.description: Draw horizontal borders.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_BordersInner
functions.description: Draw inner borders.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_BordersInnerH
functions.description: Draw horizontal borders between rows.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_BordersInnerV
functions.description: Draw vertical borders between columns.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_BordersOuter
functions.description: Draw outer borders.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_BordersOuterH
functions.description: Draw horizontal borders at the top and bottom.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_BordersOuterV
functions.description: Draw vertical borders on the left and right sides.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_BordersV
functions.description: Draw vertical borders.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_ContextMenuInBody
functions.description: Right-click on columns body/contents will display table context menu.By default it is available in TableHeadersRow.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_Hideable
functions.description: Enable hiding/disabling columns in context menu.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_HighlightHoveredColumn
functions.description: Highlight column headers when hovered (may evolve into a fuller highlight.)

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_NoClip
functions.description: Disable clipping rectangle for every individual columns(reduce draw command count, items will be able to overflow into other columns).Generally incompatible with TableSetupScrollFreeze.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_NoHostExtendX
functions.description: Make outer width auto-fit to columns, overriding outer_size.x value. Onlyavailable when ScrollX/ScrollY are disabled and Stretch columns are not used.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_NoHostExtendY
functions.description: Make outer height stop exactly at outer_size.y (prevent auto-extending tablepast the limit). Only available when ScrollX/ScrollY are disabled.Data below the limit will be clipped and not visible.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_NoKeepColumnsVisible
functions.description: Disable keeping column always minimally visible when ScrollX is off and tablegets too small. Not recommended if columns are resizable.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_NoPadInnerX
functions.description: Disable inner padding between columns (double inner padding ifTableFlags_BordersOuterV is on, single inner padding if BordersOuterV is off).

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_NoPadOuterX
functions.description: Default if TableFlags_BordersOuterV is off. Disable outermost padding.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_NoSavedSettings
functions.description: Disable persisting columns order, width and sort settings in the .ini file.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_PadOuterX
functions.description: Default if TableFlags_BordersOuterV is on. Enable outermost padding.Generally desirable if you have headers.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_PreciseWidths
functions.description: Disable distributing remainder width to stretched columns (width allocationon a 100-wide table with 3 columns: Without this flag: 33,33,34. With thisflag: 33,33,33).With larger number of columns, resizing will appear to be less smooth.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_Reorderable
functions.description: Enable reordering columns in header row(need calling TableSetupColumn + TableHeadersRow to display headers).

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_Resizable
functions.description: Enable resizing columns.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_RowBg
functions.description: Set each RowBg color with Col_TableRowBg or Col_TableRowBgAlt (equivalent ofcalling TableSetBgColor with TableBgTarget_RowBg0 on each row manually).

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_ScrollX
functions.description: Enable horizontal scrolling. Require 'outer_size' parameter of BeginTable tospecify the container size. Changes default sizing policy.Because this creates a child window, ScrollY is currently generallyrecommended when using ScrollX.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_ScrollY
functions.description: Enable vertical scrolling.Require 'outer_size' parameter of BeginTable to specify the container size.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_SizingFixedFit
functions.description: Columns default to _WidthFixed or _WidthAuto (if resizable or not resizable),matching contents width.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_SizingFixedSame
functions.description: Columns default to _WidthFixed or _WidthAuto (if resizable or not resizable),matching the maximum contents width of all columns.Implicitly enable TableFlags_NoKeepColumnsVisible.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_SizingStretchProp
functions.description: Columns default to _WidthStretch with default weights proportional to eachcolumns contents widths.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_SizingStretchSame
functions.description: Columns default to _WidthStretch with default weights all equal,unless overriden by TableSetupColumn.

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_SortMulti
functions.description: Hold shift when clicking headers to sort on multiple column.TableGetColumnSortSpecs may return specs where (SpecsCount > 1).

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_SortTristate
functions.description: Allow no sorting, disable default sorting.TableGetColumnSortSpecs may return specs where (SpecsCount == 0).

functions.name: ImGui_TableFlags_Sortable
functions.description: Enable sorting. Call TableNeedSort/TableGetColumnSortSpecs to obtain sort specs.Also see TableFlags_SortMulti and TableFlags_SortTristate.

functions.name: ImGui_TableGetColumnCount
functions.description: Return number of columns (value passed to BeginTable).

functions.name: ImGui_TableGetColumnFlags
functions.description: Return column flags so you can query their Enabled/Visible/Sorted/Hoveredstatus flags. Pass -1 to use current column.

functions.name: ImGui_TableGetColumnIndex
functions.description: Return current column index.

functions.name: ImGui_TableGetColumnName
functions.description: Return "" if column didn't have a name declared by TableSetupColumn.Pass -1 to use current column.

functions.name: ImGui_TableGetColumnSortSpecs
functions.description: Sorting specification for one column of a table.Call while incrementing 'id' from 0 until false is returned.

functions.name: ImGui_TableGetHoveredColumn
functions.description: Returns hovered column or -1 when table is not hovered. Returns columns_countif the unused space at the right of visible columns is hovered.

functions.name: ImGui_TableGetRowIndex
functions.description: Return current row index.

functions.name: ImGui_TableHeader
functions.description: Submit one header cell manually (rarely used). See TableSetupColumn.

functions.name: ImGui_TableHeadersRow
functions.description: Submit a row with headers cells based on data provided to TableSetupColumn+ submit context menu.

functions.name: ImGui_TableNeedSort
functions.description: Return true once when sorting specs have changed since last call,or the first time. 'has_specs' is false when not sorting.

functions.name: ImGui_TableNextColumn
functions.description: Append into the next column (or first column of next row if currently inlast column). Return true when column is visible.

functions.name: ImGui_TableNextRow
functions.description: Append into the first cell of a new row.

functions.name: ImGui_TableRowFlags_Headers
functions.description: Identify header row (set default background color + width of its contentsaccounted different for auto column width).

functions.name: ImGui_TableRowFlags_None
functions.description: For TableNextRow.

functions.name: ImGui_TableSetBgColor
functions.description: Change the color of a cell, row, or column.See TableBgTarget_* flags for details.

functions.name: ImGui_TableSetColumnEnabled
functions.description: Change user-accessible enabled/disabled state of a column, set to false tohide the column. Note that end-user can use the context menu to change thisthemselves (right-click in headers, or right-click in columns body withTableFlags_ContextMenuInBody).

functions.name: ImGui_TableSetColumnIndex
functions.description: Append into the specified column. Return true when column is visible.

functions.name: ImGui_TableSetupColumn
functions.description: Use to specify label, resizing policy, default width/weight, id,various other flags etc.

functions.name: ImGui_TableSetupScrollFreeze
functions.description: Lock columns/rows so they stay visible when scrolled.

functions.name: ImGui_TextColored
functions.description: Shortcut for PushStyleColor(Col_Text, color); Text(text); PopStyleColor();

functions.name: ImGui_TextFilter_Draw
functions.description: Helper calling InputText+TextFilter_Set

functions.name: ImGui_TextLink
functions.description: Hyperlink text button, returns true when clicked.

functions.name: ImGui_TextLinkOpenURL
functions.description: Hyperlink text button, automatically open file/url when clicked

functions.name: ImGui_TextWrapped

functions.name: JS_Window_SetForeground

functions.name: JS_Window_SetParent

functions.name: JS_Window_SetScrollPos
functions.description: Parameters:* scrollbar: "v" (or "SB_VERT", or "VERT") for vertical scroll, "h" (or "SB_HORZ" or "HORZ") for horizontal.

functions.name: JS_Zip_Entry_CompressFile

functions.name: JS_Zip_Entry_CompressMemory

functions.name: JS_Zip_Entry_ExtractToFile

functions.name: JS_Zip_Entry_ExtractToMemory

functions.name: JS_Zip_Entry_OpenByIndex

functions.name: JS_Zip_Entry_OpenByName
functions.description: Opens an entry by name in the zip archive.

functions.name: JS_Zip_ErrorString
functions.description: Returns a descriptive string for the given error code.

functions.name: JS_Zip_Extract
functions.description: Extracts an existing Zip file to the specified folder.

functions.name: JS_Zip_ListAllEntries
functions.description: Returns the number of entries and a zero-separated and double-zero-terminated string of entry names.

functions.name: JS_Zip_Open
functions.description: Opens a zip archive using the given mode, which can be either "READ" or "WRITE" (or simply 'r' or 'w').

functions.name: Llm_Do
functions.description: Do. Call this function to run one ReaLlm cycle. Use this function to run ReaLlm on arbitrary time intervals e.g. from a deferred script.

functions.name: Llm_GetPaths
functions.description: Get paths. Returns a string of the form "start:fx#1.fx#2...;track:fxs;...;end:fxs" where track is the track number and fx is the fx index. The string is truncated to pathStringOut_sz. 1-based indexing is used. If no MediaTrack* start is provided, all monitored input tracks are used. If no MediaTrack* end is provided, all hardware output tracks are used. If includeFx is true, the fx indices are included.

functions.name: Llm_GetSafed
functions.description: Get safed. Returns a string of the form "track:fx;track:fx;..." where track is the track number and fx is the fx index. The string is truncated to safeStringOut_sz. 1-based indexing is used. The string is followed by a | delimited list of fx names that have been set safed.

functions.name: Llm_GetVersion
functions.description: Get version. Returns the version of the plugin as integers and the commit hash as a string. The string is truncated to commitOut_sz.

functions.name: Llm_SetClearSafe
functions.description: Set clear safe. Set clear_manually_safed_fx = true to clear manually safed fx

functions.name: Llm_SetKeepPdc
functions.description: Set keep pdc

functions.name: Llm_SetMonitoringFX
functions.description: Set to include MonitoringFX. In REAPER land this means the fx on the master track record fx chain. Indexed as fx# + 0x1000000, 0-based.

functions.name: Llm_SetParameterChange
functions.description: Set parameter change. Set val1 = val2 to clear change. Set parameter_index = -666 to clear all changes. Use this function to set parameter changes between values val1 and val2 for fx_name and parameter_index instead of disabling the effect. Use custom fx names to identify individual fx.

functions.name: Llm_SetPdcLimit
functions.description: Set pdc limit as factor of audio buffer size.

functions.name: Llm_SetSafed
functions.description: Set safed. Set isSet = true to safe fx name. Set isSet = false to unsafe fx name.

functions.name: MCULive_GetButtonValue
functions.description: Get current button state.

functions.name: MCULive_GetDevice
functions.description: Get MIDI input or output dev ID. type 0 is input dev, type 1 is output dev. device < 0 returns number of MCULive devices.

functions.name: MCULive_GetEncoderValue
functions.description: Returns zero-indexed encoder parameter value. 0 = lastpos, 1 = lasttouch

functions.name: MCULive_GetFaderValue
functions.description: Returns zero-indexed fader parameter value. 0 = lastpos, 1 = lasttouch, 2 = lastmove (any fader)

functions.name: MCULive_GetMIDIMessage
functions.description: Gets MIDI message from input buffer/queue. Gets (pops/pulls) indexed message (status, data1, data2 and frame_offset) from queue and retval is total size/length left in queue. E.g. continuously read all indiviual messages with deferred script. Frame offset resolution is 1/1024000 seconds, not audio samples. Long messages are returned as optional strings of byte characters. msgIdx -1 returns size (length) of buffer. Read also non-MCU devices by creating MCULive device with their input.

functions.name: MCULive_Map
functions.description: Maps MCU Live device# button# to REAPER command ID. E.g. reaper.MCULive_Map(0,0x5b, 40340) maps MCU Rewind to "Track: Unsolo all tracks". Or remap button to another button if your MCU button layout doesnt play nicely with default MCULive mappings. By default range 0x00 .. 0x2d is in use. Button numbers are second column (prefixed with 0x) e.g. '90 5e' 0x5e for 'transport

functions.name: MCULive_Reset
functions.description: Reset device. device < 0 resets all and returns number of devices.

functions.name: MCULive_SendMIDIMessage
functions.description: Sends MIDI message to device. If string is provided, individual bytes are not sent. Returns number of sent bytes.

functions.name: MCULive_SetButtonPassthrough
functions.description: Set button as MIDI passthrough.

functions.name: MCULive_SetButtonPressOnly
functions.description: Buttons function as press only by default. Set false for press and release function.

functions.name: MCULive_SetButtonValue
functions.description: Set button led/mode/state. Value 0 = off,1 = blink, 0x7f = on, usually.

functions.name: MCULive_SetDefault
functions.description: Enables/disables default out-of-the-box operation.

functions.name: MCULive_SetDisplay
functions.description: Write to display. 112 characters, 56 per row.

functions.name: MCULive_SetEncoderValue
functions.description: Set encoder to value 0 ... 1.0. Type 0 = linear, 1 = track volume, 2 = pan. Returns scaled value.

functions.name: MCULive_SetFaderValue
functions.description: Set fader to value 0 ... 1.0. Type 0 = linear, 1 = track volume, 2 = pan. Returns scaled value.

functions.name: MCULive_SetMeterValue
functions.description: Set meter value 0 ... 1.0. Type 0 = linear, 1 = track volume (with decay).

functions.name: NF_AnalyzeMediaItemPeakAndRMS
functions.description: This function combines all other NF_Peak/RMS functions in a single one and additionally returns peak RMS positions. Lua example codehere. Note: It's recommended to use this function with ReaScript/Lua as it provides reaper.array objects. If using this function with other scripting languages, you must provide arrays in thereaper.arrayformat.

functions.name: NF_AnalyzeTakeLoudness
functions.description: Full loudness analysis. retval: returns true on successful analysis, false on MIDI take or when analysis failed for some reason. analyzeTruePeak=true: Also do true peak analysis. Returns true peak value in dBTP and true peak position (relative to item position). Considerably slower than without true peak analysis (since it uses oversampling). Note: Short term uses a time window of 3 sec. for calculation. So for items shorter than this shortTermMaxOut can't be calculated correctly. Momentary uses a time window of 0.4 sec.

functions.name: NF_AnalyzeTakeLoudness2
functions.description: Same asNF_AnalyzeTakeLoudnessbut additionally returns shortTermMaxPos and momentaryMaxPos (in absolute project time). Note: shortTermMaxPos and momentaryMaxPos indicate the beginning of timeintervalls, (3 sec. and 0.4 sec. resp.).

functions.name: NF_AnalyzeTakeLoudness_IntegratedOnly
functions.description: Does LUFS integrated analysis only. Faster than full loudness analysis (NF_AnalyzeTakeLoudness) . Use this if only LUFS integrated is required. Take vol. env. is taken into account. See:Signal flow

functions.name: NF_Base64_Decode
functions.description: Returns true on success.

functions.name: NF_Base64_Encode
functions.description: Input string may contain null bytes in REAPER 6.44 or newer. Note: Doesn't allow padding in the middle (e.g. concatenated encoded strings), doesn't allow newlines.

functions.name: NF_ClearGlobalStartupAction
functions.description: Returns true if global startup action was cleared successfully.

functions.name: NF_ClearProjectStartupAction
functions.description: Returns true if project startup action was cleared successfully.

functions.name: NF_ClearProjectTrackSelectionAction
functions.description: Returns true if project track selection action was cleared successfully.

functions.name: NF_DeleteTakeFromItem
functions.description: Deletes a take from an item. takeIdx is zero-based. Returns true on success.

functions.name: NF_GetGlobalStartupAction
functions.description: Gets action description and command ID number (for native actions) or named command IDs / identifier strings (for extension actions /ReaScripts) if global startup action is set, otherwise empty string. Returns false on failure.

functions.name: NF_GetMediaItemAverageRMS
functions.description: Returns the average overall (non-windowed) dB RMS level of active channels of an audio item active take, post item gain, post take volume envelope, post-fade, pre fader, pre item FX.Returns -150.0 if MIDI take or empty item.

functions.name: NF_GetMediaItemMaxPeak
functions.description: Returns the greatest max. peak value in dBFS of all active channels of an audio item active take, post item gain, post take volume envelope, post-fade, pre fader, pre item FX.Returns -150.0 if MIDI take or empty item.

functions.name: NF_GetMediaItemMaxPeakAndMaxPeakPos
functions.description: SeeNF_GetMediaItemMaxPeak, additionally returns maxPeakPos (relative to item position).

functions.name: NF_GetMediaItemPeakRMS_NonWindowed
functions.description: Returns the greatest overall (non-windowed) dB RMS peak level of all active channels of an audio item active take, post item gain, post take volume envelope, post-fade, pre fader, pre item FX.Returns -150.0 if MIDI take or empty item.

functions.name: NF_GetMediaItemPeakRMS_Windowed
functions.description: Returns the average dB RMS peak level of all active channels of an audio item active take, post item gain, post take volume envelope, post-fade, pre fader, pre item FX.Obeys 'Window size for peak RMS' setting in 'SWS: Set RMS analysis/normalize options' for calculation. Returns -150.0 if MIDI take or empty item.

functions.name: NF_GetProjectStartupAction
functions.description: Gets action description and command ID number (for native actions) or named command IDs / identifier strings (for extension actions /ReaScripts) if project startup action is set, otherwise empty string. Returns false on failure.

functions.name: NF_GetProjectTrackSelectionAction
functions.description: Gets action description and command ID number (for native actions) or named command IDs / identifier strings (for extension actions /ReaScripts) if project track selection action is set, otherwise empty string. Returns false on failure.

functions.name: NF_GetSWSMarkerRegionSub
functions.description: Returns SWS/S&M marker/region subtitle. markerRegionIdx: Refers to index that can be passed toEnumProjectMarkers(not displayed marker/region index). Returns empty string if marker/region with specified index not found or marker/region subtitle not set. Lua code examplehere.

functions.name: NF_GetSWS_RMSoptions
functions.description: Get SWS analysis/normalize options. SeeNF_SetSWS_RMSoptions.

functions.name: NF_ReadAudioFileBitrate
functions.description: Returns the bitrate of an audio file in kb/s if available (0 otherwise). For supported filetypes seeTagLib::AudioProperties::bitrate.

functions.name: NF_ScrollHorizontallyByPercentage
functions.description: 100 means scroll one page. Negative values scroll left.

functions.name: NF_SetGlobalStartupAction
functions.description: Returns true if global startup action was set successfully (i.e. valid action ID). Note: For SWS / S&M actions and macros / scripts, you must use identifier strings (e.g. "_SWS_ABOUT", "_f506bc780a0ab34b8fdedb67ed5d3649"), not command IDs (e.g. "47145").Tip: to copy such identifiers, right-click the action in the Actions window > Copy selected action cmdID / identifier string.NOnly works for actions / scripts from Main action section.

functions.name: NF_SetProjectStartupAction
functions.description: Returns true if project startup action was set successfully (i.e. valid action ID). Note: For SWS / S&M actions and macros / scripts, you must use identifier strings (e.g. "_SWS_ABOUT", "_f506bc780a0ab34b8fdedb67ed5d3649"), not command IDs (e.g. "47145").Tip: to copy such identifiers, right-click the action in the Actions window > Copy selected action cmdID / identifier string.Only works for actions / scripts from Main action section. Project must be saved after setting project startup action to be persistent.

functions.name: NF_SetProjectTrackSelectionAction
functions.description: Returns true if project track selection action was set successfully (i.e. valid action ID). Note: For SWS / S&M actions and macros / scripts, you must use identifier strings (e.g. "_SWS_ABOUT", "_f506bc780a0ab34b8fdedb67ed5d3649"), not command IDs (e.g. "47145").Tip: to copy such identifiers, right-click the action in the Actions window > Copy selected action cmdID / identifier string.Only works for actions / scripts from Main action section. Project must be saved after setting project track selection action to be persistent.

functions.name: NF_SetSWSMarkerRegionSub
functions.description: Set SWS/S&M marker/region subtitle. markerRegionIdx: Refers to index that can be passed toEnumProjectMarkers(not displayed marker/region index). Returns true if subtitle is set successfully (i.e. marker/region with specified index is present in project). Lua code examplehere.

functions.name: NF_SetSWS_RMSoptions
functions.description: Set SWS analysis/normalize options (same as running action 'SWS: Set RMS analysis/normalize options'). targetLevel: target RMS normalize level (dB), windowSize: window size for peak RMS (sec.)

functions.name: NF_TakeFX_GetFXModuleName
functions.description: Deprecated, seeTakeFX_GetNamedConfigParm/'fx_ident' (v6.37+). SeeBR_TrackFX_GetFXModuleName. fx: counted consecutively across all takes (zero-based).

functions.name: NF_UpdateSWSMarkerRegionSubWindow
functions.description: Redraw the Notes window (call if you've changed a subtitle viaNF_SetSWSMarkerRegionSubwhich is currently displayed in the Notes window and you want to appear the new subtitle immediately.)

functions.name: NF_Win32_GetSystemMetrics
functions.description: Equivalent to win32 API GetSystemMetrics(). Note: Only SM_C[XY]SCREEN, SM_C[XY][HV]SCROLL and SM_CYMENU are currently supported on macOS and Linux as of REAPER 6.68. Check theSWELL source codefor up-to-date support information (swell-wnd.mm, swell-wnd-generic.cpp).

functions.name: ReaPack_AboutInstalledPackage

functions.name: ReaPack_AboutRepository

functions.name: ReaPack_BrowsePackages

functions.name: ReaPack_CompareVersions

functions.name: ReaPack_EnumOwnedFiles

functions.name: ReaPack_FreeEntry

functions.name: ReaPack_GetEntryInfo

functions.name: ReaPack_GetOwner

functions.name: ReaPack_GetRepositoryInfo

functions.name: ReaPack_ProcessQueue
